- title "Flags"

%p Here are the product flags currently in the system. When a new product line is created several flags can be attached to it, these allow the public to filter the products on display so that they can easily find a list of suitable items. Examples of sensible flags are: Spoil Yourself, Front Fastening, Pocketed.

%table.interactive_table
  %thead
    %tr
      %th Position
      %th Title
      %th Blurb
      %th Image
      %th{:colspan => '3'} Actions
  %tbody
    - for flag in @flags
      %tr
        %td= h flag.position
        %td= h flag.title
        %td= h flag.blurb
        %td= image_tag flag_path(flag, :format => :png)
        %td= link_to 'Show', flag
        %td= link_to 'Edit', edit_flag_path(flag)
        %td= link_to 'Destroy', flag, :confirm => 'Are you sure?', :method => :delete

%p
  %strong Choices:
  = link_to "New Flag", new_flag_path

